I've narrowed it down to IE8 working when the css is written like this: "backgroundPositionY" and not this "background-position-y".  

So this works in firefox:
scrollorama.animate('#home', {
            duration: 1100, property: 'background-position-y', start: 0, end: -400
        });

And only this works in IE8:
scrollorama.animate('#home', {
                duration: 1100, property: 'backgroundPositionY', start: 0, end: -400
            });

I'm currently trying to figure out how I can get both to work....any ideas would be helpful!
Thanks

Probably not ideal, but I got it working with the following:

<script>
        var ie8 = false;
    </script>


```
<!--[if IE 8]>
    <script>
        ie8 = true;
    </script>
<![endif]-->
```

Then I wrapped my js in the following to use both types of css syntax:

if (ie8 == false) {
    //code using background-position-y
} else {
    //code using backgroundPositionY
}

